snippet.textDisplay: Although it seems impossible,  I drank 15 to about 22 beers everyday for at least 25 years.  A ate just ‘ok,’ nothing too healthy nor unhealthy.  But rode a bike at least 12 miles a day and walked probably about >4 to 6 miles, on average.   I had some mild liver pain for about 10 years but always had good blood work.   I had a slightly enlarged liver and a small amount of Fatty Liver.   I stopped drinking now about 7 years ago only because it became a waste of money and I was basically never getting very drunk.   Knock wood but I am completely ‘unscathed.’  Kinda amazing!
